he help of VIKOR method. In Figure 4 AHP application interface can be seen. In Figure 5 AHP Ap plication on Superdecision Program interface for this problem can be seen too. Figure 4. AHP Application Flow Chart AGRICULTURAL RISK ANALYSIS OF TURKEYIMPROVINGPRODUCTIVITY AND EFFICIENCYCRITERIA SETâ€¢Domestic Demand of Productâ€¢Export Demand of Productâ€¢Global Value of Productâ€¢Local Value of Productâ€¢Unit Cost of Productionâ€¢Unit Domestic Price of Productâ€¢Unit Export Price of ProductAvrupa Bilim ve Teknoloji Dergisi e-ISSN: 2148 -2683 506 Figure 5 . AHP Application on Superdecision Program. After pairwise comparisons and finishing each steps each criteria weights are found in Table 2. Global value of product has the highest weight and unit export price of product , export demand of product, domestic demand o f product , local value of product, unit domestic price of product are sorted orderly. Table 2. Subjective Weights O f Criterias Criteria Normalized Weights Domestic demand of product 14.3% Export demand of product 19.4% Global value of product 27.2% Local value of product 9.4% Unit domestic price of product 8.2% Unit export price of product 21.5% According to t he AHP application, evaluations of the agricultural engineers in 9 scale matrixes are used to evaluate the relative weights of each group by pairwise comparisons. Table 2 shows the obtained results. After determining the weights of six risk parameters by AHP, the evaluations of each risk parameter of Turkish agriculture VIKOR is applied. In the first step of VIKOR weights of each risk parameter are used. In the following step, the best ğ‘“ğ‘—âˆ— and the worst ğ‘“ğ‘—âˆ’ values of all risk parameter ratings are determined by equations which are mentioned above. The normalized distance is calculated for each alternatives as shown in Table 3. European Journal of Science and Technology e-ISSN: 2148 -2683 507 Table 3. Normalized Distances Of Risk Par ameters. Criteria Normalized Weights Domestic demand of 